deck: Located in Los Angeles, this small press publisher has a big interest in publishing highly stylized comics, from a variety of artists. DAPshow, formerly known as DAP Productions and DAPshow Press, is most known for it's anthologies Sweet Treats and the Gothology series.
description:
Origin

DAPshow was officially founded as a comics publisher 2008. Before that, DAPshow went by DAP Productions and produced live action shorts.

Founders

  • Doug Harvey: That guy that drew that fast food fighter pic.
  • Justin King: Co-Creator of Gothology Comics and Sweet Treats.
  • Jack Sullivan: Co-Creator of Gothology Comics.

Partner as of 2012

  • Nina Boyce: Co-Creator of Sweet Treats, Creator of Applewood and Sweet Meats.

Releases

Art Books

  • Kingsized - Justin King (2008)
  • Starbound - Doug Harvey (2009)

Minis

  • Diver Helmet Girl and Shark Head Boy - Nina Boyce (2012)
  • Plants - Nina Boyce (2015)
  • A Poot Most Fine - Nina Boyce/Justin King (2015)

Comics

  • Physicist Roundtable - Justin King (2008)
  • Beverly Beehive - Sarah Fowlie (2011)

Anthologies/Zines

  • Gothology: The Eternal Sad (2009)
  • Gothology: Misery Loves Company (2010)
  • Cat Odes (2010)
  • Sweet Treats (2015)
  • Sweet Meats (2016)

Webcomics

DAPshow has hosted a variety of webcomics, starting in 2010.

List of current comics hosted on DAPshow

  • Fritz Fargo - Sarah Fowlie (2010 - Present)
  • Applewood - Nina Boyce/Justin King (2013 - Present)
  • A Little Wicked - Arianna Fahrenkamp (2015 - Present)
  • M-Zero-Oh - Tofu Beast (2013 - Present)
  • Moon Marauders - Anna Bowles (2012 - 2013)
name: DAPshow
